HEADWORD: leopards bane
<hw>leop"ard's bane`</hw> <pr>(l⟦ecr⟧p"⟦etil⟧rdz b⟦amac⟧n`)</pr>
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A name of several harmless plants,
as <spn>Arnica montana</spn> (<spn>Arnica acaulis</spn> syn.
<spn>Doronicum acaule</spn>), <spn>Senecio Doronicum</spn>, and
<spn>Paris quadrifolia</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> leopardbane, leopard's-bane.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>leopardwood</ent>⟦br⟧
